{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:40:47.939968+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Both write methods (`create_or_update_file` and `push_files`) are returning **403 Forbidden** errors, meaning the provided GitHub token lacks write/push permissions to this repository. Unfortunately, I cannot make the actual commit.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of What's Needed for Issue #3\n\n**Issue:** Add an FAQ page to the Docusaurus sidebar.\n\n### Current State\n\n1. **`docs/faq.md`** — ✅ Already exists with proper Docusaurus frontmatter:\n   ```markdown\n   ---\n   id: faq\n   title: FAQ\n   ---\n   # FAQ\n   Frequently asked questions will be documented here.\n   ```\n\n2. **`sidebars.js`** — ❌ Needs to be updated. Current content:\n   ```js\n   module.exports = {\n     tutorialSidebar: [\n       'intro',\n       'getting-started',\n       'installation',\n       'versioning'\n     ]\n   };\n   ```\n\n### Required Change\n\nUpdate `sidebars.js` to add `'faq'` to the sidebar array:\n\n```js\nmodule.exports = {\n  tutorialSidebar: [\n    'intro',\n    'getting-started',\n    'installation',\n    'versioning',\n    'faq'\n  ]\n};\n```\n\n### Why it matters\nDocusaurus uses `sidebars.js` to determine which docs appear in the sidebar navigation. Without `'faq'` in the array, the FAQ page exists in the `docs/` folder but won't show up in the site's navigation.\n\n### Validation\nThe `Makefile` target `validate` runs `python3 scripts/validate_repo.py`, which checks:\n- Required files exist (`README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `package.json`, `docusaurus.config.js`, `sidebars.js`, `docs/intro.md`)\n- JS config files contain `module.exports`\n\nThe proposed change passes all these checks — it only adds an existing doc ID to the sidebar array.\n\n---\n\n**Limitation:** I was unable to commit the change due to insufficient GitHub token permissions (both file create/update and push endpoints return 403). A repository maintainer will need to apply this one-line change to `sidebars.js` manually.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 557, "prompt_tokens": 9717, "total_tokens": 10274, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 102, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9344, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0006804834, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001958934, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00048459}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780965631-zg01wCWFYtVZlykuqIbC", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9d2-e4fa-73c0-84be-6aae061de763-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9717, "output_tokens": 557, "total_tokens": 10274, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9344}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 102}}}}]}}}
